\begin_layout Standard
To calculate the equilibrium risk prima, we first find the market-capitalization
 weights.
 Using a sample of 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

 months, we define the market capitalization of portfolio 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 at time 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

 as
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
c_{it}=s_{it}n_{it},
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{it}$
\end_inset

 is the average firm size and 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{it}$
\end_inset

 is the total number of firms at time 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

.
 Then we define the market-capitalization weight for firm 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 at time 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

 as 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
w_{it}=\frac{c_{it}}{\sum_{j=1}^{m}c_{it}}.
\]

\end_inset

In carrying out Black-Litterman allocation model, we use 
\begin_inset Formula $w_{t}$
\end_inset

 as our vector of weights when investing for period 
\begin_inset Formula $t+1$
\end_inset

.
 Setting 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma=2.5$
\end_inset

 and letting 
\begin_inset Formula $\Sigma_{t}$
\end_inset

 be the covariance matrix of observed returns (from the beginning of the
 window until time 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

), we apply reverse optimization.
 This procedure yields
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\pi_{t}=\gamma\Sigma_{t}w_{t}.
\]

\end_inset

We can interpret 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{t}$
\end_inset

 as the mean returns implied by the market -- under the assumption of market
 equilibrium -- based on the information available at time 
\begin_inset Formula $t.$
\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To obtain the equilibrium risk prima from 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{t},$
\end_inset

 we subtract the risk-free rate, 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{f}$
\end_inset

 (for this project we use the monthly LIBOR rate at time 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

).
 To obtain the historical risk prima, we take the average of the difference
 vector 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu-r_{f}.$
\end_inset

 
\end_layout

